The easiest way to solve this problem is to invert the Vandermonde system:

**Definition (Vandermonde)** The _Vandermonde matrix_ associated with $n$ distinct points $x_0,â€¦,x_m âˆˆ ð”½$
is the square matrix
$$
V := \begin{bmatrix} 1 & x_1 & â‹¯ & x_1^{n-1} \\
                    â‹® & â‹® & â‹± & â‹® \\
                    1 & x_m & â‹¯ & x_m^{n-1}
                    \end{bmatrix} âˆˆ ð”½^{m Ã— n}
$$
