Note that $V$ encodes the linear map from coefficients to values at a grid, that is,
$$
Vðœ = \Vectt[c_0 + c_1 x_1 + â‹¯ + c_{n-1} x_1^{n-1}, â‹®, c_0 + c_1 x_m + â‹¯ + c_{n-1} x_m^{n-1}] = \Vectt[p(x_1),â‹®,p(x_m)].
$$

In the square case (where $m=n$), the coefficients of the polynomial that interpolates $f$ are given by $ðœ = V^{-1} ðŸ$, so that
$$
